Thomas Woodrow Wilson was an American politician and academic who served as the 28th President of the United States from 1913 to 1921.

Biography[]

Thomas Woodrow Wilson was born on December 28, 1856. Wilson became the president of the United States in 1913. During his presidency, WW1 was happening Europe. Wilson joined the Entente after Germany tried to convince Mexico to attack the US. Wilson and the Entente defeated the Central Powers in 1918. Woodrow Wilson died on February 3, 1924.
